<subSubSection id="C322B8883A17FF8EFF0AEF9AFE05FDD8" pageId="23" pageNumber="1156" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B87EB033A17FF8EFF0AEF9AFCE9FED5" blockId="23.[178,1086,219,270]" pageId="23" pageNumber="1156">
Redescription: Body length 
<quantity id="4CC046E63A17FF8EFDF1EF9AFD7CFF28" box="[585,714,219,240]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.05" metricValueMax="4.2" metricValueMin="3.9" pageId="23" pageNumber="1156" unit="mm" value="4.05" valueMax="4.2" valueMin="3.9">3.9-4.2 mm</quantity>
; length of forebody 
<quantity id="4CC046E63A17FF8EFC01EF9AFB8CFF28" box="[953,1082,219,240]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" metricValueMax="2.4" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="23" pageNumber="1156" unit="mm" value="2.3" valueMax="2.4" valueMin="2.2">2.2-2.4 mm</quantity>
. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation id="1303F7863A17FF8EFE85EFB9FE31FED6" box="[317,391,248,270]" captionStart="Figs 53-59" captionStartId="21.[178,218,1243,1265]" captionTargetBox="[184,1087,212,1220]" captionTargetId="figure-1@21.[178,1091,212,1233]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 53-59: Lithocharis distinguenda CAMERON (59: lectotype): (53) habitus; (54) forebody; (55) male sternite VII; (56) male sternite VIII; (57-58) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (59) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 53-54: 1.0 mm; 55-59: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184200" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184200/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="1156">Fig. 53</figureCitation>
. External characters (
<figureCitation id="1303F7863A17FF8EFDD9EFB9FD67FED6" box="[609,721,248,270]" captionStart="Figs 53-59" captionStartId="21.[178,218,1243,1265]" captionTargetBox="[184,1087,212,1220]" captionTargetId="figure-1@21.[178,1091,212,1233]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 53-59: Lithocharis distinguenda CAMERON (59: lectotype): (53) habitus; (54) forebody; (55) male sternite VII; (56) male sternite VIII; (57-58) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (59) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 53-54: 1.0 mm; 55-59: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184200" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184200/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="1156">Figs 53-54</figureCitation>
) as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3890803A17FF8EFCACEFB8FCEFFED5" authorityName="Kraatz" authorityYear="1859" box="[788,857,248,270]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lithocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="1156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vilis">
<emphasis id="B94C37113A17FF8EFCACEFB8FCEFFED5" box="[788,857,248,270]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="1156">L. vilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B87EB033A17FF8EFF0AEE5CFE05FDD8" blockId="23.[178,1085,285,512]" pageId="23" pageNumber="1156">
♂: sternite VII (
<figureCitation id="1303F7863A17FF8EFED8EE5CFE1BFEEB" box="[352,429,285,307]" captionStart="Figs 53-59" captionStartId="21.[178,218,1243,1265]" captionTargetBox="[184,1087,212,1220]" captionTargetId="figure-1@21.[178,1091,212,1233]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 53-59: Lithocharis distinguenda CAMERON (59: lectotype): (53) habitus; (54) forebody; (55) male sternite VII; (56) male sternite VIII; (57-58) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (59) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 53-54: 1.0 mm; 55-59: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184200" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184200/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="1156">Fig. 55</figureCitation>
) moderately transverse, posterior margin with shallow median excision of broadly trapezoid shape, this excision with a comb of approximately 25 long palisade setae; sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="1303F7863A17FF8EFE56EE19FD88FEB6" box="[494,574,344,366]" captionStart="Figs 53-59" captionStartId="21.[178,218,1243,1265]" captionTargetBox="[184,1087,212,1220]" captionTargetId="figure-1@21.[178,1091,212,1233]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 53-59: Lithocharis distinguenda CAMERON (59: lectotype): (53) habitus; (54) forebody; (55) male sternite VII; (56) male sternite VIII; (57-58) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (59) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 53-54: 1.0 mm; 55-59: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184200" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184200/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="1156">Fig. 56</figureCitation>
) transverse, postero-median portion extensively without pubescence, posterior margin moderately deep, broadly V-shaped; aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="1303F7863A17FF8EFF01EED3FE9FFE70" box="[185,297,402,424]" captionStart="Figs 53-59" captionStartId="21.[178,218,1243,1265]" captionTargetBox="[184,1087,212,1220]" captionTargetId="figure-1@21.[178,1091,212,1233]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 53-59: Lithocharis distinguenda CAMERON (59: lectotype): (53) habitus; (54) forebody; (55) male sternite VII; (56) male sternite VIII; (57-58) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (59) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 53-54: 1.0 mm; 55-59: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184200" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184200/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="1156">Figs 57-59</figureCitation>
) approximately 
<quantity id="4CC046E63A17FF8EFE77EED2FDAAFE70" box="[463,540,403,424]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="23" pageNumber="1156" unit="mm" value="0.7">0.7 mm</quantity>
long, apically bifid in ventral view, at base of ventral process with a long string-shaped appendix best visible in lateral view; dorso-lateral apophyses with straight, short, and thin apices; internal structures distinctly sclerotized and of distinctive shapes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C322B8883A17FF8EFF0AED4EFE3EFD0D" pageId="23" pageNumber="1156" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B87EB033A17FF8EFF0AED4EFE3EFD0D" blockId="23.[178,1085,527,725]" pageId="23" pageNumber="1156">
Comparative notes: As can be inferred from the similar external and male sexual characters, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3890803A17FF8EFEC9ED6CFDA7FD9A" authorityName="Cameron" authorityYear="1928" box="[369,529,557,578]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lithocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="1156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="distinguenda">
<emphasis id="B94C37113A17FF8EFEC9ED6CFDA7FD9A" box="[369,529,557,578]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="1156">L. distinguenda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C3890803A17FF8EFD54ED6CFC85FD9A" authorityName="Kraatz" authorityYear="1859" box="[748,819,557,578]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lithocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="1156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vilis">
<emphasis id="B94C37113A17FF8EFD54ED6CFC85FD9A" box="[748,819,557,578]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="1156">L. vilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it differs by the shape of the posterior excision of the male sternite VII, the less numerous and longer palisade setae at the posterior margin of the male sternite VII, by the shape and chaetotaxy of the male sternite VIII, as well as by the smaller aedeagus with a bifid apex, with smaller and differently shaped dorso-lateral apophyses, and with internal structures of distinctive shapes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
